      },
      "date": "2011-11-01 07:58:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think this test could safely be revived if our tar patch had some string in it that verified it can handle sparse files efficiently.  Then the sanity.sh test could run \"strings $(which tar) | grep {magic string}\" to see if the patch was applied, or alternately skip the test.",
