    {
      "id": "d2356ebe065184f9ee6c954b473dc337516d218c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-14 22:25:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(4 inline comments)\n\nSome minor style fixes needed.\n\nHowever, more importantly is the question of whether tar is patched or not?  Is the goal of this test to verify the test environment has a patched version of tar installed, or that the version of tar we build has the patch applied, or that the patch is actually working?\n\nIt would be preferable to only run the test if we know the version of tar is (or should be) functional, either by the tar version number or checking the tar binary for a specific string, and otherwise not causing the test to fail.  Otherwise, testing will fail in some environments with unpatched tar versions...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "ae10360c908942b2cc4e9aeffaaa25cc409fe21b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 137,
        "name": "Richard Henwood",
        "email": "richard.henwood@intel.com",
        "username": "rhenwood",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-23 18:59:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHowever, more importantly is the question of whether tar is patched or not? Is the goal of this test to verify the test environment has a patched version of tar installed, or that the version of tar we build has the patch applied, or that the patch is actually working?\n\nThis is an excellent point. The use case for patched tar is 'file level back-up and restore of an MDT'\n\nGiven this, the test should only run on an MDS. File-level restore is only available since 2.3 - but you might want to backup on any 2.x MDT.\n\nFor 2.3 RHEL6.3 is the only supported server. This has a patched tar for sparse files included.\n\nIf we back-port this patch to 2.1.x series, then we should need to use our own tar with that.\n\nI request to: Land this patch on Master.\n\n\n It would be preferable to only run the test if we know the version of tar is (or should be) functional, either by the tar version number or checking the tar binary for a specific string, and otherwise not causing the test to fail. Otherwise, testing will fail in some environments with unpatched tar versions...\n\nI don't think it is necessary to test the tar version. As stated above, Master only supports RHEL6.3, 6.3 has a patched tar included. This test could be judged as redundant given this - but I think it is a worth while regression test.\n\n\nI'll address your comments and resubmit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
